          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Emergency EU Summit</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/Ursula-von-der-Leyen-Volodymyr-Zelensky-EU-summit-Brussels.png" alt="European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen speaks with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky as they arrive for an EU summit in Brussels" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen speaks with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky as they arrive for an EU summit in Brussels. Credits: Omar Havana / Associated Press</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">European leaders held emergency talks in Brussels yesterday to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-03-2025-h2-2-strengthen-support-for-ukraine" target="_blank">strengthen support for Ukraine</a> and bolster defense. This follows President Trump’s pivot away from European alliances. Polish PM Donald Tusk urged Europe to rise to the challenge, emphasizing its strength against Russia. The Polish President said Ukraine should take the mineral agreement. The European Commission proposed over $150 Bn in joint borrowing for military spending.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">However, the EU faces hurdles, including Hungary’s resistance and decades of reliance on US security. French President Macron suggested extending France’s nuclear deterrence to Europe. This drew mixed reactions. Meanwhile, Germany plans to lift borrowing limits to fund defense. British PM Keir Starmer called for a "coalition of the willing" to propose a peace plan.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Trump's demand for NATO allies to spend more on defense has pressured Europe to increase military funding. The EU is considering an investment of $840 Bn. President Zelensky urged the bloc to act swiftly, warning Europe can no longer rely on Washington. The Ukrainian ambassador to the UK, Valerii Zaluzhnyi, bluntly said that "the US under Donald Trump is destroying world order long questioned by Russia and other actors."</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
