            <strong>🇵🇦 Panama President Mulino says Trump is ‘lying’ about reclaiming the canal</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Panama's President José Raul Mulino has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-07-03-2025-b2-5-refuted-president-donald-trumps-claims" target="_blank">refuted President Donald Trump's claims</a> about "reclaiming" the Panama Canal. During his congressional address, Trump stated that the US was "taking back" the canal to enhance national security. He cited an agreement in which a US firm, BlackRock Inc., would purchase a controlling stake in a Chinese-operated port consortium.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Mulino rejected these claims, stating that Panama has maintained complete control over the canal since it was handed over by the US in 1999. Trump’s repeated references to the canal’s “reclamation” have sparked tensions with Panama. Panama has also dismissed the notion of Chinese influence over the canal. While the US constructed the canal in the early 20th century, Panama has managed it independently since the handover.</p>
        </mj-text>
